{
  "texts": [
    "Natural Questions(NQ) (Kwiatkowski et al., 2019) is a very well-known dataset in the NLU field.The given text describes a structured question and a corresponding Wikipedia page.",
    "The page is annotated with a long answer, typically a paragraph, and a short answer consisting of one or more entities.",
    "If there is no long or short answer, it is labelled as empty.",
    "Due to the reliability of the Google search engine and its vast amount of data, many scholars have used this dataset to train RALM, such as Wang et al. (2023c), Izacard et al. (2022) and Ram et al. (2023).",
    "HotpotQA(HQA) (Yang et al., 2018) stores information about multihop questions and provides sentence-level supporting facts needed for inference."
  ]
}